    "description": "Hindalco Industries is actively seeking a talented and motivated Manufacturing Engineer to join our dynamic team in Pimpri-Chinchwad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Hindalco Industries:\nHindalco Industries is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pimpri-Chinchwad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Hindalco Industries!",
